Brent Crude’s Premium to WTI Widens a Third Day to More Than $23

-- B y   J o h n   B u c k l e y
-- 
2011-08-18T07:46:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-18/brent-crude-s-premium-to-wti-widens-a-third-day-to-more-than-23.html
North Sea Brent crude futures’
premium to West Texas Intermediate, the U.S. benchmark, widened
for a third day to more than $23 a barrel.  The difference between front-month Brent on ICE Futures
Europe exchange and WTI on the  New York Mercantile Exchange  was
$23.06 a barrel at 8:45 a.m. London time, compared with $22.87
at settlement yesterday, according to data compiled by
Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 John Buckley  in Amsterdam at 
 johnbuckley@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at 
